X_n
X
E(X_n) \rightarrow E(X)
|X_n - X| \in L_1
E(|X_n - X|) < \infty
E(X_n^2),E(X^2)<\infty
|E[X_n-X]|\leq E[|X_n-X|[ \leq E[(X_n-X)^2] = E[X_n^2]-2E[X_nX]+E[X^2]
E[X_nX]=Cov[X_n,X]+E[X_n]E[X]
(i.e, |COV[X,Y]| \leq \sigma_X\sigma_y)
E[X_n]E[X]-\sigma_{X_n}\sigma_X\leq E[X_nX]\leq E[X_n]E[X]+\sigma_{X_n}\sigma_X
n\rightarrow \infty
0\leq E|X_n-X| \leq E[X_n^2]+E[X^2]-2\{[E[X]]^2-\sigma_X\lim\limits_{n\rightarrow\infty}\sigma_{X_n}\}
X_n
|X_n-X| \in \mathcal{L^1}
E[|X_n-X|]=\infty
